  "title": "Step 5: Generate responses with the LLM.",
  "description": "Retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) is an architecture used\nto augment large language models (LLMs) with additional data\nso that they can generate more accurate responses.\nYou can implement RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) in your generative AI applications\nby combining an LLM with a retrieval system powered by MongoDB Vector Search.",
